Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{240%g} the pan. Season and fry until browned on each side and cooked through, ~{13-15%mins}. Turn every 2-3 mins. Set aside. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1} and slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Drain and rinse the @Butter Beans{1%carton} in a sieve. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put the pan back on high heat with a drizzle of oil if needed (no need to clean).

Once hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{3-4%mins} each side. Once cooked, season with @salt and @pepper.

Add the garlic and stir fry, ~{30%secs}. Transfer the veg to a #bowl{}. Set aside for later.

In the (now empty) pan, combine the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, butter beans, @Vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet} and @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}.

> Add less 'Nduja if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir in the @Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

Mix well and bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer the sauce until slighty thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

When the sauce is cooked, stir in the @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%g}, @Butter{20%g} and half the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}.

Taste and season with @salt and @pepper if needed.

When the chicken is cooked, slice into 1cm thick slices.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and spoon over the veg and remaining sauce from the pan.

Top with the sliced chicken and courgette rounds, then sprinkle with the remaining cheese and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish. Enjoy!